7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 761, L.D. 1953, “An Act to Ensure
10 Public Access to Conservation Land by Providing Protections from Liability to
11 Landowners”
12 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 7 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 14 in L.D.) by
13 striking out the following: "any" and inserting the following: 'one or more'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment clarifies that additional protection from liability for a landowner or
1188 other grantor who grants, and a holder or grantee who accepts, an easement or other legal
1199 instrument that includes or makes an express grant of perpetual public access over premises
2200 is for the public to pursue one or more, rather than any, recreational or harvesting activities.
